{"title_page": "Francisco de la Puebla Gonz\u00e1lez", "text_new": "{{Infobox Christian leader\n| type        = Bishop\n| honorific-prefix = Most Reverend\n| name        = Francisco de la Puebla Gonz\u00e1lez\n| title       = Bishop of Santiago de Chile\n| image       = \n| alt         = \n| caption     = \n| church      = [[Catholic Church]]\n| archdiocese = \n| diocese     = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Santiago de Chile|Diocese of Santiago de Chile]]\n| see         = \n| term        = 1694\u20131704\n| predecessor = [[Bernardo de Carrasco y Saavedra]]\n| successor   = [[Luis Francisco Romero]]\n<!--   Orders   -->\n| ordination     = 17 Dec 1667\n| ordained_by    = \n| consecration   = 29 Jul 1695\n| consecrated_by = \n| cardinal       =\n| rank           = \n<!--   Personal details   -->\n| birth_date    = 9 Jun 1643 \n| birth_place   = Pradera de Sepulveda, [[Spain]]\n| death_date    = 21 Jan 1704 (age 60)\n| death_place   = [[Santiago de Chile]]\n| previous_post = \n| nationality   = Spanish\n}}\n\n'''Francisco de la Puebla Gonz\u00e1lez''' (1643\u20131704) was a Roman Catholic prelate who served as [[Archbishop of Santiago (Chile)|Bishop of Santiago de Chile]] (1694\u20131704).<ref name=CathHierFranPueGon>[http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/bishop/bpuegon.html \"Bishop Francisco de la Puebla Gonz\u00e1lez\"] ''[[Catholic-Hierarchy.org]]''. David M. Cheney. Retrieved September 25, 2016</ref><ref name=CathHierSantChile>[http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/dsacl.html \"Archdiocese of Santiago de Chile\"] ''[[Catholic-Hierarchy.org]]''. David M. Cheney. Retrieved February 29, 2016</ref><ref name=GCathSantChile>[http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/ztia1.htm#5511 \"Metropolitan Archdiocese of Santiago\"] ''GCatholic.org''. Gabriel Chow. Retrieved February 29, 2016</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nFrancisco de la Puebla Gonz\u00e1lez was born in Pradera de Sepulveda, [[Spain]] on 9 Jun 1643 and ordained a priest on 17 Dec 1667.<ref name=CathHierFranPueGon />\nOn 8 Nov 1694, he was appointed during the papacy of [[Pope Innocent XII]] as [[Archbishop of Santiago (Chile)|Bishop of Santiago de Chile]].<ref name=CathHierFranPueGon />\nOn 29 Jul 1695, he was consecrated bishop.<ref name=CathHierFranPueGon /> \nHe served as Bishop of Santiago de Chile until his death on 21 Jan 1704.<ref name=CathHierFranPueGon /> \nWhile bishop, he was the principal co-consecrator of [[Juli\u00e1n Cano y Tevar]], [[Bishop of Urgell]] (1695); and [[Tom\u00e1s Reluz]], [[Bishop of Oviedo]] (1697).<ref name=CathHierFranPueGon />\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-rel|ca}}\n{{succession box\n| title  = [[Archbishop of Santiago (Chile)|Bishop of Santiago de Chile]]\n| years  = 1694\u20131704\n| before = [[Bernardo de Carrasco y Saavedra]]\n| after  = [[Luis Francisco Romero]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Puebla Gonz\u00e1lez, Francisco de la}}\n[[Category:17th-century Roman Catholic bishops]]\n[[Category:18th-century Roman Catholic bishops]]\n[[Category:Bishops appointed by Pope Innocent XII]]\n[[Category:1643 births]]\n[[Category:1704 deaths]]\n\n{{RC-bishop-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Christian leader\n| type        = Bishop\n| honorific-prefix = Most Reverend\n| name        = Francisco de la Puebla Gonz\u00e1lez\n| title       = Bishop of Santiago de Chile\n| image       = \n| alt         = \n| caption     = \n| church      = [[Catholic Church]]\n| archdiocese = \n| diocese     = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Santiago de Chile|Diocese of Santiago de Chile]]\n| see         = \n| term        = 1694\u20131704\n| predecessor = [[Bernardo de Carrasco y Saavedra]]\n| successor   = [[Luis Francisco Romero]]\n<!--   Orders   -->\n| ordination     = 17 Dec 1667\n| ordained_by    = \n| consecration   = 29 Jul 1695\n| consecrated_by = \n| cardinal       =\n| rank           = \n<!--   Personal details   -->\n| birth_date    = 9 Jun 1643 \n| birth_place   = Pradera de Sepulveda, [[Spain]]\n| death_date    = 21 Jan 1704 (age 60)\n| death_place   = [[Santiago de Chile]]\n| previous_post = \n| nationality   = Spansih\n}}\n\n'''Francisco de la Puebla Gonz\u00e1lez''' (1643\u20131704) was a Roman Catholic prelate who served as [[Archbishop of Santiago (Chile)|Bishop of Santiago de Chile]] (1694\u20131704).<ref name=CathHierFranPueGon>[http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/bishop/bpuegon.html \"Bishop Francisco de la Puebla Gonz\u00e1lez\"] ''[[Catholic-Hierarchy.org]]''. David M. Cheney. Retrieved September 25, 2016</ref><ref name=CathHierSantChile>[http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/dsacl.html \"Archdiocese of Santiago de Chile\"] ''[[Catholic-Hierarchy.org]]''. David M. Cheney. Retrieved February 29, 2016</ref><ref name=GCathSantChile>[http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/ztia1.htm#5511 \"Metropolitan Archdiocese of Santiago\"] ''GCatholic.org''. Gabriel Chow. Retrieved February 29, 2016</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nFrancisco de la Puebla Gonz\u00e1lez was born in Pradera de Sepulveda, [[Spain]] on 9 Jun 1643 and ordained a priest on 17 Dec 1667.<ref name=CathHierFranPueGon />\nOn 8 Nov 1694, he was appointed during the papacy of [[Pope Innocent XII]] as [[Archbishop of Santiago (Chile)|Bishop of Santiago de Chile]].<ref name=CathHierFranPueGon />\nOn 29 Jul 1695, he was consecrated bishop.<ref name=CathHierFranPueGon /> \nHe served as Bishop of Santiago de Chile until his death on 21 Jan 1704.<ref name=CathHierFranPueGon /> \nWhile bishop, he was the principal co-consecrator of [[Juli\u00e1n Cano y Tevar]], [[Bishop of Urgell]] (1695); and [[Tom\u00e1s Reluz]], [[Bishop of Oviedo]] (1697).<ref name=CathHierFranPueGon />\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-rel|ca}}\n{{succession box\n| title  = [[Archbishop of Santiago (Chile)|Bishop of Santiago de Chile]]\n| years  = 1694\u20131704\n| before = [[Bernardo de Carrasco y Saavedra]]\n| after  = [[Luis Francisco Romero]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Puebla Gonz\u00e1lez, Francisco de la}}\n[[Category:17th-century Roman Catholic bishops]]\n[[Category:18th-century Roman Catholic bishops]]\n[[Category:Bishops appointed by Pope Innocent XII]]\n[[Category:1643 births]]\n[[Category:1704 deaths]]\n\n{{RC-bishop-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Tbfhhvuv", "label": "safe", "comment": "Spansih -> Spanish", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Francisco_de_la_Puebla_Gonz%C3%A1lez"}
{"title_page": "Plectocomia pierreana", "text_new": "{{Speciesbox\n|image =\n|genus = Plectocomia\n|species = pierreana\n|authority = [[Odoardo Beccari|Becc.]], Webbia; Raccolta de Scritti Botanici. Florence, 3: 236, 1910\n|synonyms = *''P. barthiana'' Hodel\n*''P. cambodia'' [[Fran\u00e7ois Gagnepain|Gagnep.]] ex [[Paul Henri Lecomte|Lecomte]]\n*''P. kerriana'' Beccari. \n}}\n\n'''''Plectocomia pierreana''''' is a species of liana in the [[Arecaceae]], or palm tree, family.  It is a spiny climber, with either a single stem or a cluster of stems up to 35m in length, stems are 1 to 9cm in diameter.<ref name=\"DyPhon\">{{cite book |last1=Dy Phon |first1=Pauline |title=Plants Used In Cambodia/Plantes utilis\u00e9es au Cambodge |date=2000 |publisher=Imprimerie Olympic |location=Phnom Penh|page=304|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=InD2RAAACAAJ}}</ref><ref name=\"Pei\">{{cite journal |last1=Pei Shengji (\u88f4\u76db\u57fa) |last2=Chen Sanyang (\u9648\u4e09\u9633) |last3=Guo Lixiu (\u90ed\u4e3d\u79c0) |last4=Henderson |first4=Andrew |title=ARECACEAE (PALMAE), \u68d5\u6988\u79d1  zong l\u00fc ke |journal=Pei Shengji & Chen Sanyang, eds., Fl. Reipubl. Popularis Sin. |date=1991 |volume=13 |issue=1 |page=134-5 |url=http://flora.huh.harvard.edu/china/mss/volume23/Flora_of_China_Vol_23_Arecaceae.pdf |accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>  Its spines are up to 2cm long.\n\nThe palm is native to [[Thailand]], [[Cambodia]], [[Laos]], [[Vietnam]] and [[China|Zh\u014dnggu\u00f3/China]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Dransfield |first1=J. |last2=Barfod |first2=A.S. |last3=Pongsattayapipat |first3=R. |title=A preliminary checklist to Thai Palms |journal=Thai For. Bull. (Bot.) |date=2004 |volume=32 |page=32\u201372 |url=https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Anders_Barfod2/publication/256388501_A_preliminary_checklist_to_Thai_Palms/links/00b49522f06df71c22000000/A-preliminary-checklist-to-Thai-Palms.pdf |accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Tran\">{{cite web |last1=Tran |first1=Thi Phuong Anh |last2=Nguyen |first2=Khac Khoi |title=''Plectocomia pierreana Becc. (Arecaceae Schutz-sch.) a new species for the flora of Vietnam'' [Abstract in English] |url=http://www.vjs.ac.vn/index.php/vjbio/article/view/5414 |website=Vietnam Academy of Science and Technology, Tap Chi Sinh Hoc, Journal of Biology |accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=IPNI |title=Plectocomia pierreanna |url=https://www.ipni.org/n/669206-1 |website=International Plant Name Index |accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\nIt occurs in the dense forests and stunted forest of Cambodia, particularly in [[Kampot Province|Kampot]] and [[Kampong Chhnang Province|Kampong Chhnang]] provinces<ref name=\"DyPhon\" />.\nGrowing in [[Preah Monivong National Park|Bokor National Park]], in Kampot, it occurs in the stunted forest community, called ''for\u00eat sempervirente basse de montagne'' by [[Pauline Dy Phon]], that occurs around 920m, though the plant possibly occurs up to 1014m.<ref name=\"rundel\">{{cite journal |last1=Rundel|first1=Philip W. |last2=Middleton |first2=David J. |title=Flora of Bokor Plateau, southeastern Cambodia: a homage to [[Pauline Dy Phon]] |journal=Cambodian Journal of Natural History |date=2017 |volume=1 |page=17-37}}</ref>\nIt has also been reported as very common in [[Phnom Kulen National Park]], [[Siem Reap Province]], Cambodia, growing particularly in the Evergreen Forest community.<ref name=\"hayes\">{{cite web |last1=Hayes |first1=Benjamin, & others |title=A Biodiversity Assessment of Phnom Kulen National Park, with Recommendations for Management. 2013 |url=https://www.rufford.org/files/11488-1%20Detailed%20Final%20Report_0.pdf |website=The Rufford Foundation |publisher=Integrated Solutions Asia Cooperation |accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\nIn Vietnam it has been identified in [[L\u00e0o Cai Province|L\u00e0o Cai]], [[Tuy\u00ean Quang Province|Tuy\u00ean Quang]] and [[V\u0129nh Ph\u00fac Province|V\u0129nh Ph\u00fac]] provinces.<ref name=\"Tran\" />\nPresent in [[Yunnan]], [[Guangxi]] and [[Guangdong]] provinces in China, it is found in lowland to montane rainforests below 1200m, growing rapidly and abundantly.<ref name=\"Pei\" /><ref name=\"Zheng\">{{cite journal |last1=Zheng Yaxian |last2=Lv Wenhua |title=Rattan Cane Modified with Polyethylene Glycol Melamine-Urea-Formaldehyde Resin |journal=BioResources |date=2015 |volume=10 |issue=3 |page=4663-73 |url=https://ojs.cnr.ncsu.edu/index.php/BioRes/article/viewFile/BioRes_10_3_4663_Zheng_Rattan_Cane_Resin/3629}}</ref>\n\nIn Cambodia, the plant is known as ''phdau tra\u00e8hs'', ''phdau ach mo\u00ebn'' or ''phdao sno'', and the stalk/trunk is used to make ropes and in basketwork.<ref name=\"DyPhon\" /><ref name=\"hayes\" />\nProducing large rattan, between 20-40mm in diameter, out of which furniture, baskets, fish-traps, &c., are made, ''wai teleuk'' (local name in [[Lao language]], ''wai'' means rattan) is commercially exploited in Laos.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Ketphanh |first1=Sounthone |title=Non-wood forest products in Lao People's Democratic Republic |date=1995 |publisher=Beyond Timber: Social, Economic and Cultural Dimensions of Non-Wood Forest Products in Asia and the Pacific. Proceedings of  a  Regional Expert Consultation 28 November- 2 December 1994. FAO/RAP, Bangkok. Patrick B. Durst & Ann Bishop ed. Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations. Regional Office for Asia and the Pacific (RAP) |location=Bangkok |page=215-26 |url=https://pdfs.semanticscholar.org/ea7c/eb0b16f3c84b161773f8bd62b049a32eca6b.pdf#page=222}}</ref>\nIts official name in China is \u94a9\u53f6\u85e4  ''gou ye teng''.<ref name=\"Pei\" />  In China there is a view that as a source of rattan, it has inferior physical and mechanical properties.<ref name=\"Zheng\" />\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q15468973}}\n\n[[Category:Biota of Cambodia]]\n[[Category:Flora of Cambodia]]\n[[Category:Flora of China]]\n[[Category:Flora of Indo-China]]\n[[Category:Flora of Vietnam]]\n[[Category:Plectocomia|pierreana]]\n[[Category:Trees of Cambodia]]\n[[Category:Trees of China]]\n[[Category:Trees of Vietnam]]\n\n{{palm-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Speciesbox\n|image =\n|genus = Plectocomia\n|species = pierreana\n|authority = [[Odoardo Beccari|Becc.]], Webbia; Raccolta de Scritti Botanici. Florence, 3: 236, 1910\n|synonyms = *''P. barthiana'' Hodel\n*''P. cambodia'' [[Fran\u00e7ois Gagnepain|Gagnep.]] ex [[Paul Henri Lecomte|Lecomte]]\n*''P. kerriana'' Beccari. \n}}\n\n'''''Plectocomia pierreana''''' is a species of liana in the [[Arecaceae]], or palm tree, family.  It is a spiny climber, with either a single stem or a cluster of stems up to 35m in length, stems are 1 to 9cm in diameter.<ref name=\"DyPhon\">{{cite book |last1=Dy Phon |first1=Pauline |title=Plants Used In Cambodia/Plantes utilis\u00e9es au Cambodge |date=2000 |publisher=Imprimerie Olympic |location=Phnom Penh}}</ref><ref name=\"Pei\">{{cite journal |last1=Pei Shengji (\u88f4\u76db\u57fa) |last2=Chen Sanyang (\u9648\u4e09\u9633) |last3=Guo Lixiu (\u90ed\u4e3d\u79c0) |last4=Henderson |first4=Andrew |title=ARECACEAE (PALMAE), \u68d5\u6988\u79d1  zong l\u00fc ke |journal=Pei Shengji & Chen Sanyang, eds., Fl. Reipubl. Popularis Sin. |date=1991 |volume=13 |issue=1 |page=134-5 |url=http://flora.huh.harvard.edu/china/mss/volume23/Flora_of_China_Vol_23_Arecaceae.pdf |accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>  Its spines are up to 2cm long.\n\nThe palm is native to [[Thailand]], [[Cambodia]], [[Laos]], [[Vietnam]] and [[China|Zh\u014dnggu\u00f3/China]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Dransfield |first1=J. |last2=Barfod |first2=A.S. |last3=Pongsattayapipat |first3=R. |title=A preliminary checklist to Thai Palms |journal=Thai For. Bull. (Bot.) |date=2004 |volume=32 |page=32\u201372 |url=https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Anders_Barfod2/publication/256388501_A_preliminary_checklist_to_Thai_Palms/links/00b49522f06df71c22000000/A-preliminary-checklist-to-Thai-Palms.pdf |accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Tran\">{{cite web |last1=Tran |first1=Thi Phuong Anh |last2=Nguyen |first2=Khac Khoi |title=''Plectocomia pierreana Becc. (Arecaceae Schutz-sch.) a new species for the flora of Vietnam'' [Abstract in English] |url=http://www.vjs.ac.vn/index.php/vjbio/article/view/5414 |website=Vietnam Academy of Science and Technology, Tap Chi Sinh Hoc, Journal of Biology |accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=IPNI |title=Plectocomia pierreanna |url=https://www.ipni.org/n/669206-1 |website=International Plant Name Index |accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\nIt occurs in the dense forests and stunted forest of Cambodia, particularly in [[Kampot Province|Kampot]] and [[Kampong Chhnang Province|Kampong Chhnang]] provinces<ref name=\"DyPhon\" />.\nGrowing in [[Preah Monivong National Park|Bokor National Park]], in Kampot, it occurs in the stunted forest community, called ''for\u00eat sempervirente basse de montagne'' by [[Pauline Dy Phon]], that occurs around 920m, though the plant possibly occurs up to 1014m.<ref name=\"rundel\">{{cite journal |last1=Rundel|first1=Philip W. |last2=Middleton |first2=David J. |title=Flora of Bokor Plateau, southeastern Cambodia: a homage to [[Pauline Dy Phon]] |journal=Cambodian Journal of Natural History |date=2017 |volume=1 |page=17-37}}</ref>\nIt has also been reported as very common in [[Phnom Kulen National Park]], [[Siem Reap Province]], Cambodia, growing particularly in the Evergreen Forest community.<ref name=\"hayes\">{{cite web |last1=Hayes |first1=Benjamin, & others |title=A Biodiversity Assessment of Phnom Kulen National Park, with Recommendations for Management. 2013 |url=https://www.rufford.org/files/11488-1%20Detailed%20Final%20Report_0.pdf |website=The Rufford Foundation |publisher=Integrated Solutions Asia Cooperation |accessdate=5 April 2020}}</ref>\nIn Vietnam it has been identified in [[L\u00e0o Cai Province|L\u00e0o Cai]], [[Tuy\u00ean Quang Province|Tuy\u00ean Quang]] and [[V\u0129nh Ph\u00fac Province|V\u0129nh Ph\u00fac]] provinces.<ref name=\"Tran\" />\nPresent in [[Yunnan]], [[Guangxi]] and [[Guangdong]] provinces in China, it is found in lowland to montane rainforests below 1200m, growing rapidly and abundantly.<ref name=\"Pei\" /><ref name=\"Zheng\">{{cite journal |last1=Zheng Yaxian |last2=Lv Wenhua |title=Rattan Cane Modified with Polyethylene Glycol Melamine-Urea-Formaldehyde Resin |journal=BioResources |date=2015 |volume=10 |issue=3 |page=4663-73 |url=https://ojs.cnr.ncsu.edu/index.php/BioRes/article/viewFile/BioRes_10_3_4663_Zheng_Rattan_Cane_Resin/3629}}</ref>\n\nIn Cambodia, the plant is known as ''phdau tra\u00e8hs'', ''phdau ach mo\u00ebn'' or ''phdao sno'', and the stalk/trunk is used to make ropes and in basketwork.<ref name=\"DyPhon\" /><ref name=\"hayes\" />\nProducing large rattan, between 20-40mm in diameter, out of which furniture, baskets, fish-traps, &c., are made, ''wai teleuk'' (local name in [[Lao language]], ''wai'' means rattan) is commercially exploited in Laos.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Ketphanh |first1=Sounthone |title=Non-wood forest products in Lao People's Democratic Republic |date=1995 |publisher=Beyond Timber: Social, Economic and Cultural Dimensions of Non-Wood Forest Products in Asia and the Pacific. Proceedings of  a  Regional Expert Consultation 28 November- 2 December 1994. FAO/RAP, Bangkok. Patrick B. Durst & Ann Bishop ed. Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations. Regional Office for Asia and the Pacific (RAP) |location=Bangkok |page=215-26 |url=https://pdfs.semanticscholar.org/ea7c/eb0b16f3c84b161773f8bd62b049a32eca6b.pdf#page=222}}</ref>\nIts official name in China is \u94a9\u53f6\u85e4  ''gou ye teng''.<ref name=\"Pei\" />  In China there is a view that as a source of rattan, it has inferior physical and mechanical properties.<ref name=\"Zheng\" />\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q15468973}}\n\n[[Category:Biota of Cambodia]]\n[[Category:Flora of Cambodia]]\n[[Category:Flora of China]]\n[[Category:Flora of Indo-China]]\n[[Category:Flora of Vietnam]]\n[[Category:Plectocomia|pierreana]]\n[[Category:Trees of Cambodia]]\n[[Category:Trees of China]]\n[[Category:Trees of Vietnam]]\n\n{{palm-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Brunswicknic", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plectocomia_pierreana"}
